        "content": "<p>I've been doing some doodling to understand Lean's type hierarchy.</p>\n<p>Not saying this one would be <em>particularly</em> helpful to anyone but I wonder if it captures the right intuitions?</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/jAzl0HRTNXrIpje1E2wLbAfJ/Untitled-2025-02-02-1522-copy.png.png\">Untitled-2025-02-02-1522 copy.png.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/jAzl0HRTNXrIpje1E2wLbAfJ/Untitled-2025-02-02-1522-copy.png.png\" title=\"Untitled-2025-02-02-1522 copy.png.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"4000x2969\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/jAzl0HRTNXrIpje1E2wLbAfJ/Untitled-2025-02-02-1522-copy.png.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div><p>Note this only deals with concrete universes (not stuff polymorphic over them). It also doesn't do anything with types being dependent.</p>\n<p>But broadly, does it appear correct? Is anything misleading or flat out wrong?</p>\n<p>Thanks.</p>",
